---
/**
 * Why this matters — three positions reflecting the new framing:
 * replacing both the consultant and the overpriced legacy software,
 * with AI used to clear infrastructure friction (not as marketing).
 */
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="how">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <rect x="4.5" y="6" width="10" height="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <rect x="9.5" y="12" width="10" height="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <path d="M3.5 19L20.5 5" stroke="#F0A91A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="butt"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">01</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">Replaces the overpriced consultant <span class="why-stat__amp">and</span> software.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Run an economic impact study yourself, on your own data, when the question gets asked. Look back historically for a longitudinal analysis, or model forward to plan a budget, grant, or capital project. One annual subscription, unlimited runs, every geography included: reservation, county, state, or the full country.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <rect x="3.5" y="14" width="3.5" height="7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <rect x="8.75" y="10" width="3.5" height="11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <rect x="14" y="6" width="3.5" height="15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <rect x="19.25" y="12" width="3.5" height="9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <circle cx="15.75" cy="6" r="1.6" fill="#F0A91A"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">02</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">Unlock more value from data your team already has.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Bring your administrative records, payroll detail, and budget data. We pair it with current high-frequency public and private sources, and some we construct ourselves, to surface insights national averages from a 2017 input-output table can't reach.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="why-stat">
      <span class="why-stat__icon" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M12 3L13.6 9.4L20 11L13.6 12.6L12 19L10.4 12.6L4 11L10.4 9.4L12 3Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linejoin="miter"/>
          <circle cx="12" cy="11" r="1.5" fill="#F0A91A"/>
        </svg>
      </span>
      <p class="why-stat__num">03</p>
      <p class="why-stat__k">AI built for messy data and small regions.</p>
      <p class="why-stat__v">Cedar reads uploads from any department, flags every assumption the model is about to use, and writes the source record. Trained specifically for economic impact studies, including the small regions and tribal governments that off-the-shelf models can't handle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
